title: Railworks TS2014  IHH Class 56
description:
Class 56 Diesel Locomotive


Heavy freight locomotive used by British Railways

Four livery variations including:

- BR Blue

- BR Grey

- BR Railfreight Grey/Yellow

- BR Sector Grey with selectable logo's

- EWS Maroon

- BR Large Logo

- Romanian and BR Built Styles

Lights and Working Wipers

New Sound Set

Five interesting scenarios:

[56] Grid lines    = Class 56 power for a heavy train of scottish coal for Darlington power station.

[56] Grid Iron     = Heavy iron ore train from Thrislington to Dunston Staithes.

[56] Grid MGR      = MGR coal train from Oxford to Didcot and return.

[56] York Freeroam = A selection of 56's and various trains in York yard. 

[56] Rainy Night   = MGR coal train on The Port Road.
